status_message:
"Your boy is smart, funny, and open hearted, and he got some flex in him. And I didn't see it at first cause he was always actin' out, always full of the corner talk, talking sh*t to hide himself. He can go a lot of places and do a lot of things in his life-- be out there in the world in a way that didn't happen for you and me… He's a lot of things. A lot of good things. Before you know it, he might surprise all of us given a half a chance. But he ain't made for them corners, man."

To all the fathers and father figures, Happy Father's Day.

"Couple weeks from now, you're gonna be in some district somewhere with 11 or 12 uniforms looking to you for everything. And some of them are gonna be good police. Some of them are gonna be young and stupid. A few are gonna be pieces of sh*t. But all of them will take their cue from you. You show loyalty, they learn loyalty. You show them it's about the work, it'll be about the work. You show them some other kinda game, then that's the game they'll play. I came on in the Eastern, and there was a piece-of-sh*t lieutenant hoping to be a captain, piece-of-sh*t sergeants hoping to be lieutenants. Pretty soon we had piece-of-sh*t patrolmen trying to figure the job for themselves. And some of what happens then is hard as hell to live down. Comes a day you're gonna have to decide whether it's about you or about the work." - Daniels

status_message: "Listen to me, you f*ck. You did a lot of shit here. You played a lot of f*cking cards. And you made a lot of f*cking people do a lot of f*cking things they didn't want to do. But f*ck if I'm gonna stand here and say you did a single f*cking thing to get a police shot. You did not do this, you f*cking hear me? This is not on you. No it isn't, asshole. Believe it or not, everything isn't about you. And the motherf*cker saying this, he hates your guts, McNulty. So you know if it was on you, I'd be the son of a bitch to say so. Sh*t went bad. status_message: "Where's Wallace? Where the f*** is Wallace? Huh? Huh? String? String? Look at me! Where the f*** is Wallace? HUH!? I don't want this Payless-wearing motherf***er representing me. I'mma get my own man. So just get back in your car and get the f*** back down south."- D'Angelo
"Same f***-ups in the same shit detail, workin' out of the same sh**house kind of office. You people lack for personal growth, you know that?"- Lester

"Fool, what do you think? That we know anything about who gives money? That we give a damn about who they are or what they want? We have no way of running down them or their stories. We don't care. We just cash the damn cheques, count the votes and move on."- Clay Davis
"What the f*** do you wanna hear? That you strong enough to do this by yourself? Gettin' clean's easy part. Now comes life."- Waylon
"You see these east-side motherf***er's over here? I want'chu to extend to these motherf***er's all the hospitality west Baltimore is famous for."- Stringer
"Ah then, tragically, you will have wasted yet another day in a life you've already misspent in the service of the City of Baltimore."- Lester
"I go at him respectable. He put that goddamn shotgun in my face, man. I'm looking at two goddamn tubes of the Harbor Tunnel staring right at me."- Bubbles
"Shoot, the way y'all looking at things, ain't no victim to even speak on."- Omar
"It's like one of those nature shows. You mess with the environment, some species get f***ed out of their habitat."- Avon

"Don't matter who did what to who at this point. Fact is, we went to war and there ain't no turnin' back. I mean, sh*t, it's what war is, you know? Once you in it, you in it. If it's a lie, then we fight on that lie. But we gotta fight.."- Slim Charles

status_message: "You came into a lot of money quick. You can go to jail just as quick if I start asking the right questions. This case ends, or you are done. Hell, I don't even need you to lock up Barksdale. I can have your major debrief the detectives and type the warrants himself. This case is done." - Burrell

Guess who said this quote and you can be randomly selected to win a Wire Soundtrack. "All my people, man, my father, my uncles, It's just what we do. You just live with this shit, until you can't breathe no more. I swear to God, I was courtside for eight months, and I was freer in jail than I was at home."
"This here game is more than the rep you carry, the corner you hold. You gotta be fierce, I know that, but more than that, you gotta show some flex, give and take on both sides."- Stringer

Guess who said this quote and you can be randomly selected to win a Wire Soundtrack. "It's like one of those nature shows. You mess with the environment, some species get f**ked out of their habitat."

Who said this quote? "You know the difference between me and you? I bleed red and you bleed green. I look at you these days, String, you know what I see? I see a man without a country. Not hard enough for this right here and maybe, just maybe, not smart enough for them out there."
"If the Gods are f**king you, you find a way to f**k them back. It's Baltimore, gentlemen; the Gods will not save you."- Burrell
"Omar had this one ho' pullin' guns out her pu**y. That shit was unseemly, yo."- Cheese

status_message: Who said this quote? Answer correctly and you can be randomly selected to win a Wire soundtrack. "You are amoral, are you not? You are feeding off the violence and the despair of the drug trade. You're stealing from those who themselves are stealing the lifeblood from our city."
"I'm a murder police. I work murders. I don't f**k with no make-believe. I don't jerk sh*t around. I catch a murder, and I work it."- Bunk

"It sure as hell scares me. The old man always said "Live by the sword, die by the sword". All this time, he was the biggest player in Baltimore. Survived all this shit. Now, he's lying here in this bed. F**king natural causes. Scares the sh*t out of me."- Avon Barksdale
"They f*ck up, they get beat. We f*ck up, they give us pensions."- Carver

"How come they know you're police when they hook up with you. And they know you're police when they move in. And they know you're police when they decide to start a family with you. And all that shit is just fine until one day it ain't no more. One day, it's 'You should have a regular job.' and 'You need to be home at five o'clock'."- Kima

"I want what Wallace wanted. I want to start over. That's what I want. I don't care where. Anywhere. I don't give a f*ck. I just want to go somewhere, where I can breathe like regular folk. You give me that... And I'll give you them."-  D'Angelo
